bilingual.source: She had planted native plants, year after year.
bilingual.target: 她年复一年地种植本地植物。

I started doing that a year ago.

list.abstract: year（英[jɪə]，美[jɪr]），英语单词，名词，意思为年；年度；岁数。短语搭配有last year（去年），例句为“Last year, I visited a special school for students with weak sight or hearing loss.（去年，我参观了一所为视力或听力受损的学生开设的特殊学校。）” year近义词有annum。

yingyinNormal.en: How to Celebrate Chinese New Year.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如何庆祝中国年。

yingyinNormal.en: I studied for a year in Barcelona.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我在巴塞罗那念过一年书。

yingyinNormal.en: The scrutiny, the judgment. I'm partner less than a year.
yingyinNormal.zh: 监视，评判，我做合伙人还不到一年。

yingyinNormal.en: We sleep together once a year! You want other partners?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们一年才"睡"一次！你还想有其他伴侣吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Diane, any merger would require a three-year window on Chumhum.
yingyinNormal.zh: 戴安，不管怎样合并，你们三年内都不能动查查网。

yingyinNormal.en: Yes. We're very popular. There's a two-year waiting list. Sorry.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是的，这里很受欢迎，预约已经排到2年后，抱歉。

yingyinNormal.en: John Stirling? He was a 20-year veteran.He protected three presidents.
yingyinNormal.zh: 约翰·斯特林 他当了20年的总统保镖。侍卫过三位总统

yingyinNormal.en: I hate this year. What's wrong with this year?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我讨厌今年。今年有什么不对的？

yingyinNormal.en: It's the Chinese New Year.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这就是中国新年。

yingyinNormal.en: They're only taking one this year.
yingyinNormal.zh: 今年他们只录取一个。

yingyinNormal.en: Not giving raises till next year, but go on.
yingyinNormal.zh: 想加薪等明年吧，不过你继续说。

yingyinNormal.en: Who voted him our team captain this year? Us!
yingyinNormal.zh: 谁选他作我们今年的队长的？我们！

yingyinNormal.en: Every year, the school has a student showcase.
yingyinNormal.zh: 学校每年一次会举办学生科技展。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah, why don't you sleep at Maya's this year?
yingyinNormal.zh: 就是啊，为啥今年不去玛雅家过夜呢？

yingyinNormal.en: They did it at Pepper's New Year's Steve party.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他们在胡娇家的新年史蒂夫派对上也是这样。

yingyinNormal.en: So, Sophie's getting a Snapple. Like last year.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那好，送苏菲一瓶果汁，跟去年的礼物一样。

yingyinNormal.en: Local young entrepreneur of the year, two years running.
yingyinNormal.zh: 本地年度青年企业家得主，连续两年。

yingyinNormal.en: It's an industry worth an estimated $1.5 billion a year.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是个每年创造大约十五亿美元产值的工业。

yingyinNormal.en: Nearby, Kensington Palace is open to the public year-round.
yingyinNormal.zh: 附近的肯辛顿宫全年开放给公众参观。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh wow, so it's a really positive year. A really good year.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这一年真好。非常好的一年。

examination_example.sentence: 49 <highlight>years</highlight> later, Apollo 11 reached the moon, and the famed newspaper published an apology to Goddard.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 49年后，阿波罗11号到达月球，这家著名的报纸发表了对Goddard的道歉。

examination_example.sentence: Globally, road accidents kill more people every <highlight>year</highlight> than any infectious disease.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在全球范围内，道路事故每年造成的死亡人数超过任何传染病。

examination_example.sentence: It was not popularized until <highlight>years</highlight> later.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它直到多年后才普及。

examination_example.sentence: They have experienced a gradual decline since the <highlight>year</highlight> of 2017.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 自2017年以来，他们经历了一个逐渐下降的过程。

examination_example.sentence: They rise and fall from <highlight>year</highlight> to <highlight>year</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它们每年都有升有降。

examination_example.sentence: "We've been saying for <highlight>years</highlight> that the budget for maintaining historic monuments is too low," Gady said.
examination_example.sentence_trans: “我们多年来一直在说，维护历史遗迹的预算太低了，”Gady说。

examination_example.sentence: One famous experiment in the 1960s involved 3- to 6-<highlight>year</highlight>-old children.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 1960年代的一项著名实验涉及三至六岁的儿童。

examination_example.sentence: In his later <highlight>years</highlight>, Marconi exerted a tremendous influence on all aspects of people's life.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 马可尼晚年对人们生活的方方面面都产生了巨大的影响。

examination_example.sentence: Police and fire services will spend the next 48 hours assessing the "security and safety" of the 850-<highlight>year</highlight>-old structure.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 警察和消防部门将在接下来的48小时内评估这座有850年历史的建筑的“安保和安全”。

examination_example.sentence: The whale population has become endangered due to commercial whaling activities in recent <highlight>years</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 近年来，由于商业捕鲸活动，鲸鱼种群已濒临灭绝。

examination_example.sentence: The practice of paying children an allowance became popular in America about 100 <highlight>years</highlight> ago.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 大约在100年前，给孩子零花钱的做法开始在美国流行。

examination_example.sentence: This will be the third time you've left a job in the last five <highlight>years</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这将是你在过去五年中第三次离职。

examination_example.sentence: For <highlight>years</highlight>, parents and teachers have worried that these games might be addictive.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一段时间以来，家长和老师一直担心这些游戏可能会上瘾。

examination_example.sentence: People's changing diet over the <highlight>years</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一段时间以来人们饮食的改变。

examination_example.sentence: She describes how the definition of beauty has changed over the <highlight>years</highlight> and even from culture to culture.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 她描述了美的定义是如何随着时间的推移而改变的，甚至是从一种文化到另一种文化的转变。

examination_example.sentence: The dog is six and a half <highlight>years</highlight> old and was last seen wearing a red collar.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这只狗六岁半，最后一次被看见时戴着红领。

examination_example.sentence: It is over 100 <highlight>years</highlight> old.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它已经有100多年的历史了。

examination_example.sentence: Her mother told her to diet when she was only 8 <highlight>years</highlight> old.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 她妈妈在她只有8岁的时候就告诉她要节食。

sense_info_list.zh: 年级; 某年级的学生

examination_example.sentence: Through this program, I believe, first <highlight>year</highlight> students will lay the groundwork for future learning, exploration and social networking.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我相信，通过这个项目，一年级学生将为未来的学习、探索和社交打下基础。

examination_example.sentence: Following this, students had to complete a difficult mental math task in front of the same upper-<highlight>year</highlight> students.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 接下来，学生们必须在同样的高年级学生面前完成一项困难的数学脑力任务。

examination_example.sentence: In this study, students came into the laboratory and were asked to give a public speech in front of upper-<highlight>year</highlight> students.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在这项研究中，学生进入实验室，并且要在高年级学生面前发表公开演讲。

examination_example.sentence: It's been well documented in extensive research over the <highlight>years</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 多年来，大量的研究都证明了这一点。

examination_example.sentence: Many <highlight>years</highlight> later, Liu was noticed by public again.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 许多年以后，刘再次被公众所注意。

examination_example.sentence: In recent <highlight>years</highlight>, she has made shadow puppets based on some cartoon series and given a live streaming performance.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 近年来，她根据一些卡通系列制作了皮影戏，并进行了现场流媒体表演。

examination_example.sentence: A smoke alarm lasts about ten <highlight>years</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一个烟雾报警器大约可以用十年。

examination_example.sentence: I think about my three-<highlight>year</highlight>-old sister.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我想起了我三岁的妹妹。

examination_example.sentence: The 6-<highlight>year</highlight>-old girl, Ruby, lived in New Orleans, Louisiana.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这个6岁的女孩名叫鲁比，住在路易斯安那州的新奥尔良。

examination_example.sentence: Instead, the 19-<highlight>year</highlight>-old boy decided to do something for people who were less lucky than himself.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 相反，这个19岁的男孩决定为那些没有他幸运的人做点什么。
